m, Wiltshire, England","Melksham, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Melksham, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Brounker","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German (Rhineland-Palatinate; mainly <b>Brünker</b>): habitational name for someone from Brunken in Rhineland-Palatinate.","English: variant of   Brunger  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Brunger","meanings":["German (<b>Brünger</b>): from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Brunger</i> meaning ‘brown or shining spear’.","English (Kent): from the Middle English personal name <i>Brunger</i> (Old English <i>Brūngār</i>, with the same etymology as its ancient Germanic cognate <i>Brunger</i> in 1 above).","Altered form of Swiss German <b>Brüngger</b>: habitational name denoting someone from Brünggen in Switzerland."]},{"name":"Branker","meanings":["English (Wiltshire and Kent; also common in the West Indies): perhaps a variant of   Brunker   (see   Brunger  )."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Brounker was born in 1465, in Melksham, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Unknown Gouldinge. He died in January 1537, in his hometown, at the age of 72."},"et":{"1465–January 1537":"1465–jaanuar 1537","1470–1535":"1470–1535","1500–Female":"1500–Surnud","1510–1568":"1510–1568","1465–1537":"1465–1537","1 January 1510":"1. jaanuar 1510","1568":"1568","1535":"1535","1500":"1500","1510":"1510","1465":"1465","about 1535":"umbes 1535","about 1500":"umbes 1500","1470":"1470","January 1537":"jaanuar 1537","1537":"1537","Melksham, Wiltshire, England":"Melksham, Wiltshire, England","Melksham, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Melksham, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1465–January 1537":"1465–tammikuu 1537","1470–1535":"1470–1535","1500–Female":"1500–Kuollut","1510–1568":"1510–1568","1465–1537":"1465–1537","1 January 1510":"1. tammikuuta 1510","1568":"1568","1535":"1535","1500":"1500","1510":"1510","1465":"1465","about 1535":"noin 1535","about 1500":"noin 1500","1470":"1470","January 1537":"tammikuu 1537","1537":"1537","Melksham, Wiltshire, England":"Melksham, Wiltshire, England","Melksham, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Melksham, Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1465–January 1537":"1465–janvier 1537","1470–1535":"1470–1535","1500–Female":"1500–Décédée","1510–1568":"1510–1568","1465–1537":"1465–1537","1 January 1510":"1 janvier 1510","1568":"1568","1535":"1535","1500":"1500","1510":"1510","1465":"1465","about 1535":"environ 1535","about 1500":"environ 1500","1470":"1470","January 1537":"janvier 1537","1537":"1537","Melksham, Wiltshire, England":"Melksham, Wiltshire, Angleterre","Melksham, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Melksham, Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert Brounker est né en 1465, à Melksham, Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille avec Unknown Gouldinge. Il est décédé en ja